item.title: CVE-2018-11070|2024-09-16T19:36:17.519Z -- dell%20emc -- rsa%20bsafe%20crypto-j
item.description: RSA BSAFE Crypto-J versions prior to 6.2.4 and RSA BSAFE SSL-J versions prior to 6.2.4 contain a Covert Timing Channel vulnerability during PKCS #1 unpadding operations, also known as a Bleichenbacher attack. A remote attacker may be able to recover a RSA key.
